 
<p>
Congress has proposed a law to prohibit setting up AI systems to
<a href="https://www.commondreams.org/news/artificial-intelligence-and-nuclear-weapons">decide
whether to launch nuclear weapons</a>.
   This is not an imaginary issue: there have been proposals to do just that.
<p>
The legal technique of "no federal funds may be used" has a well-known
loophole: just find a private source of funds to do the specific job.
<a class=glossary href="/glossary.html#thug">Thugs</a> have used "<a href="https://stallman.org/archives/2014-sep-dec.html#19_October_2014_(Private_police_foundations)">police foundations</a>"
to negate laws design with that
method.

